{"id": "1416343853950046290", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "type": 0, "author_id": "877511774834917427", "author_name": ".cnork", "author_bot": false, "content": "I just checked the map of Iceland and realized that it definitely can't be her because there's only one mountain and the rest is flat.  since according to the flashbacks of the researchers you can see the pezage of the island where the church was found, you can see that the island looks like two mountains at two extremes with a lowland in the center. it is also important to note that the island is much further north than England, Scotland, and even further north than the Shetland archipelago because there is not such a low thermal climate there for such a huge level of snow to appear. but the island is not close to Iceland or Norway since Norway has a mountainous coastline that would be visible out of the corner of your eye in the flashbacks. it is also important to note that the island must be within reach of these shores because otherwise the words spoken by the ship \"Sonar\" would be a lie. therefore, looking in this zone, I found the island of Jan Mayen, which fits all the above measures. despite the fact that the lowland part of the island is narrow, this can easily be explained by the fact that in the 19th century, when the story takes place, there was no global warming on the same level as today, and therefore the island was larger and it is also worth noting that the pictures I found were taken in warm weather, which means that the ice crust that would become the place where snow would fall is not visible. if necessary, I will send you a link to the place in a personal message", "timestamp": "2025-09-13T08:44:49.178000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
